[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":49,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":58,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":69,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Edmond Penfound was born about 1500, in Bude, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas Penfound. He married Penfound about 1534, in Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 5 May 1572, in East Down, Devon, England, at the age of 73."},"et":{"about 1500–5 May 1572":"umbes 1500–5. mai 1572","1490–1544":"1490–1544","1500–1572":"1500–1572","–1574":"–1574","1536–1574":"1536–1574","1470–1544":"1470–1544","5 May 1572":"5. mai 1572","1572":"1572","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1536":"1536","after 1544":"pärast 1544","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1544":"1544","about 1534":"umbes 1534","1574":"1574","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1549":"1549","Penfound Wood, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Bude, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pen